{
  "stem": "15694.6",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then I tried to get some halves amongst them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was warned they're harder to carry-- you know, they'll fall-- they'll fall down easier.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, and when they fall, you have to pick them up and very often with the beating to go with it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So again five, and again, at the same spot, and then back.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there were so many of us, although some were exhausted and maybe that they didn't get up even if they were beaten.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm not sure there were some killed-- probably were.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there were so many of us that the wagon was soon unloaded.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when I came back to the barracks out of breath, exhausted, and in a terrible state and thinking, what, you know, of [? saving ?] [? and seeing ?] the others.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The fellow who was sitting next to my father-- a Viennese fellow-- sung a s-- you know, was singing a Viennese song.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If somebody knows any Austrian or Viennese songs, this was a famous called fiacre song.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "A fiacre is like a taxi, but with horses.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, and I was thinking what, what a thin dividing line between laughter and, and death.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Anyway, that's just one more incident from there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And another time which I was called, and I had to work outside the camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were only guarded-- we were about 50 people-- only guarded by three Ukrainians.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I thought, ah, now there's a way-- that would be a way of escaping.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But how do I get my father to come with me?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] for a moment thinking and speaking also later to my father, if we escape the others will be killed.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So he reminded me.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
